        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 1 at 4:16PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Deer Trail, or 28 miles northwest of Limon, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 30 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail may accumulate on roadways causing hazardous travel,
including I-70 near Deer Trail.

Locations impacted include...
Deer Trail and Cottonwood Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
